      {
        "position": 6,
        "title": "Petropolitan mixed high-end luggage w/premium Cat carrier features-Comfy kitty travel palace.",
        "text": "This carrier looks more like a nice piece of luggage than a carrier for kitties(Or a16lb or less)It has a wide shoulder strap as well as handles so you can comfortably and safely carry it. It's very easy to spot clean. It also includes a comfy, removable & washable pad-The pad is reversible(One side is best for use during the summer/if your cat tends to overheat & the other side is best for winter)Both cats love to be in it even at home. If I leave it out & open they'll climb in to hide, snuggle and/or nap. We did put an extra Sherpa pad in it because I thought the ladies would be more comfortable with a tad more padding. Im not a huge fan of the orange \"seatbelt\" leash thing but it could be helpful for some people, especially if your cat/dog tries to escape when you open the carrier. The ladies fit in this comfortably together & that's great although I dont recommend putting more than 2-3 small-ish cats(Weight of cats must total 16lbs or less)in one carrier, especially if your cats dont get along well. They will essentially be trapped in a small space together. I always test the cat's reaction to a new carrier just in case one of them decides they dont want to share the new space. Best to find that out long before trip day! The size of this carrier is one of the things I like most about it. While it does state it is air travel compliant/approved you may want to check with your specific airline's policies on having multiple cats in one carrier(A certain airline used to not allow more than one cat per carrier as per policy but its a good idea to check the most up to date policies. Many airlines allow 2 cats maximum as long as they don't exceed the 16lb max weight & both cats fit comfortably with plenty of space to stand up, change positions, ect. This carrier is sturdy for a soft side carrier. It feels like it's made of premium, high quality materials & it seems to be well-made. I didnt notice any chemical smells as some reviews have noted but I did remove it from the packaging and let it air out long before the girls investigated & explored it. The size & elegant aesthetics is enough to justify the slightly higher price point in my opinion. While I feel it may be a tad on the higher end of the price scale I still think it's reasonably priced.The flaps can be left up/down over the mesh ventilation screens depending on your cat's preference& how much or how little visibility your cat prefers. I usually leave them open for max ventilation since both cats are comfortable with seeing everything around us. Some cats may feel safer/prefer not seeing outside of the carrier. Many airlines have different guidelines regarding pet carrier ventilation, which is another reason to review your carrier's specific rules about traveling with pets/carrier guidelines in advance. This carrier is likely good for trevel on trains and busses too but I recommend reviewing their policies to avoid any gotcha moments on your trip. The Petropolitan is great for car trips-From quick rides to the vet & pet store to longer road trips, this carrier keeps the ladies comfy & safe, All while lookin stylish in their little travel palace.One helpful Tip-Use a small carabiner or other locking mechanismm to secure the zippers together for a little bit of added security, especially if your cat becomes houdinni when they travel.All and all, we love this carrier & I would recommend it to kitty Moms and Dads.",
