      {
        "position": 8,
        "title": "Cats Approve",
        "text": "Cats are not to scale or normal-sized cats 😂 The white one is over 5 lbs and the tabby is over 6 lbs.I took this to the vet with my tabby and got many compliments! The vet even thought the name \"Petropolitan\" was cute. I even had a friend come over to see my new kittens and she noticed and loved this carrier.I was worried in the picture that the handles and trim would be orange on the beige model. But they're not, they are definitely beige, which is good. It's also not too pink, it is definitely beige.The little flaps that you can clip up are super cute. And I like that you can keep your cat completely concealed with them closed (my vet usually has a blanket or towel to put over carriers while cats are in the waiting room).I love that it's collapsible but is still sturdy at the same time. I've had a fabric carrier before and wasn't going to get another one because it just felt like it would fall in on the cat and was flimsy. This does not feel like that at all.My cat's been scratching the netting (just for fun. She loves to play in it) and there's not even a scratch on it. It's very secure.This is a great carrier for cats! Very well-made and well thought out.",
